HEADWORD: Adroitness
<hw>A*droit"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality of being adroit;
skill and readiness; dexterity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Adroitness</qex> was as requisite as courage.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Skill</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

